are the only countries in the world

262
00:11:47,520 --> 00:11:51,000
that do not provide
any paid time off for new mothers.

263
00:11:51,080 --> 00:11:54,240
Just us
and Papua New Guinea.

264
00:11:54,320 --> 00:11:55,840
That's as unlikely a pairing

265
00:11:55,920 --> 00:11:58,000
as Sofía Vergara
and Reese Witherspoon.

266
00:11:58,080 --> 00:11:59,920
Separately, great.

267
00:12:00,000 --> 00:12:02,840
But if it's just
the two of them with no one else,

268
00:12:02,920 --> 00:12:06,240
it makes you feel like one of them
has taken her eye off the ball.

269
00:12:06,320 --> 00:12:07,920
Reese.

270
00:12:08,000 --> 00:12:10,880
In the US, here in the US,

271
00:12:10,960 --> 00:12:15,800
federal law grants workers
just 12 weeks of unpaid leave.

272
00:12:15,880 --> 00:12:18,320
And there are
some stark limits on that.

273
00:12:18,400 --> 00:12:21,040
You have to work for a company
with 50 or more employees.

274
00:12:21,120 --> 00:12:23,240
You have to have been there
for over a year.

275
00:12:23,320 --> 00:12:25,440
You have to be a full-time
salaried employee.

276
00:12:25,520 --> 00:12:28,240
So if you're a freelancer, contractor,
something like that,

277
00:12:28,320 --> 00:12:29,800
it doesn't apply to you.

278
00:12:29,880 --> 00:12:33,080
And what that means
is that 40% of workers

279
00:12:33,160 --> 00:12:35,520
are not covered
by the federal law.

280
00:12:35,600 --> 00:12:38,840
So if a worker with no paid leave
goes into labor at work,

281
00:12:38,920 --> 00:12:40,840
she better hope
it's on her lunch hour

282
00:12:40,920 --> 00:12:43,920
and that her coworkers don't mind
if the break room gets a bit messy.

283
00:12:44,000 --> 00:12:46,920
And this is not to say
that women don't take leave.

284
00:12:47,000 --> 00:12:50,080
They just have to get very creative
about doing it.

285
00:12:50,160 --> 00:12:52,920
What we have right now,
women do take maternity leave.

286
00:12:53,000 --> 00:12:54,600
It is oftentimes unpaid.

287
00:12:54,680 --> 00:12:56,720
And it is through
a patchwork system

288
00:12:56,800 --> 00:12:58,720
where they use up
their vacation time,

289
00:12:58,800 --> 00:13:00,320
they use up
their sick days.

290
00:13:00,400 --> 00:13:02,600
One woman I talked to
put her maternity leave,

291
00:13:02,680 --> 00:13:04,240
essentially,
on her credit cards.

292
00:13:04,320 --> 00:13:06,360
Now, sure,
that sounds bad,

293
00:13:06,440 --> 00:13:08,920
but on the plus side,
think of all the points she earned

294
00:13:09,000 --> 00:13:10,920
towards vacation
she can't now take

295
00:13:11,000 --> 00:13:13,160
because she has
a fucking baby.

296
00:13:13,240 --> 00:13:15,920
This is not how
it's supposed to work.

297
00:13:16,000 --> 00:13:18,040
Mothers shouldn't
have to stitch together time

298
00:13:18,120 --> 00:13:19,920
to recover from childbirth

299
00:13:20,000 --> 00:13:23,200
the same way that we plan
four-day weekends in Atlantic City.

300
00:13:23,280 --> 00:13:25,600
"I'll take
a vacation day Thursday,

301
00:13:25,680 --> 00:13:27,920
"call out sick Friday,
hit the slots Saturday,

302
00:13:28,000 --> 00:13:30,000
"win big Sunday,
and I'll never go back, baby !

303
00:13:30,080 --> 00:13:31,840
Whoo !"

304
00:13:31,920 --> 00:13:33,640
And look,

305
00:13:33,720 --> 00:13:35,920
there are women
who want to get back to work

306
00:13:36,000 --> 00:13:38,200
as soon as they can,
and that's obviously fine.

307
00:13:38,280 --> 00:13:40,320
But for many women,
the current situation

308
00:13:40,400 --> 00:13:42,960
forces them to return
well before they want to,

309
00:13:43,040 --> 00:13:44,760
like this new mother.

310
