00:15:17,960 --> 00:15:19,920
"and I was forced to leave it
right there in the hospital

346
00:15:20,000 --> 00:15:21,920
"for financial reasons.
But go ahead,

347
00:15:22,000 --> 00:15:23,920
"tell me what you had
for brunch the next day.

348
00:15:24,000 --> 00:15:25,720
"You had waffles ?

349
00:15:25,800 --> 00:15:29,120
You're incredible, Carol.
That's a great fucking story."

350
00:15:29,200 --> 00:15:31,720
And, look,

351
00:15:31,800 --> 00:15:34,920
I don't mean to suggest
that this is an issue

352
00:15:35,000 --> 00:15:37,120
that only mothers
should have to think about.

353
00:15:37,200 --> 00:15:40,040
Family leave should be thought of
as an option for both parents,

354
00:15:40,120 --> 00:15:42,240
which will take
some cultural adjustment.

355
00:15:42,320 --> 00:15:44,920
Look at Major League Baseball,
which offers all of three days off

356
00:15:45,000 --> 00:15:47,040
to players who become fathers.

357
00:15:47,120 --> 00:15:49,440
But when one of them,
the Mets' Daniel Murphy,

358
00:15:49,520 --> 00:15:51,720
actually took it,
this happened.

359
00:15:51,800 --> 00:15:54,680
This week, sports radio
skewered him

360
00:15:54,760 --> 00:15:57,920
for missing the first two games
of the season for his son's birth.

361
00:15:58,000 --> 00:16:00,680
You get your back to your team
and you play baseball.

362
00:16:00,760 --> 00:16:02,920
That's my take on it.

363
00:16:03,000 --> 00:16:05,080
What... there's nothing
you can do anyway.

364
00:16:05,160 --> 00:16:06,800
You're not breastfeeding
the kid.

365
00:16:06,880 --> 00:16:08,520
Always said, C-section
before the season starts.

366
00:16:08,600 --> 00:16:10,320
I need to be at opening day.

367
00:16:12,120 --> 00:16:14,120
Good luck selling that
to your wife.

368
00:16:14,200 --> 00:16:15,520
"Uh, listen, babe,

369
00:16:15,600 --> 00:16:17,640
"I know I play 162 games
