370
00:16:17,720 --> 00:16:19,040
"but I can't miss
a single one,

371
00:16:19,120 --> 00:16:21,040
"so let's cut that thing
out of your belly

372
00:16:21,120 --> 00:16:22,760
"so I can wear
my baggy pajamas

373
00:16:22,840 --> 00:16:25,560
and swing a cone of wood
to make a ball go far."

374
00:16:25,640 --> 00:16:29,320
So why do we have this system
in the United States ?

375
00:16:29,400 --> 00:16:33,320
Well, for a start, employers
tend to fear any sort of mandate.

376
00:16:33,400 --> 00:16:35,320
But when it comes
to family leave,

377
00:16:35,400 --> 00:16:37,760
any fears do tend
to be overblown.

378
00:16:37,840 --> 00:16:40,080
Look at the way that lawmakers
discussed our current

379
00:16:40,160 --> 00:16:42,200
12 weeks
of unpaid leave system

380
00:16:42,280 --> 00:16:44,920
back when it was proposed
in 1993.

381
00:16:45,000 --> 00:16:46,920
I want to make sure
that all of you

382
00:16:47,000 --> 00:16:50,240
who will vote for this
have no illusions.

383
00:16:50,320 --> 00:16:52,920
This bill will cost jobs.

384
00:16:53,000 --> 00:16:55,920
Today, America's businesses
are already saddled

385
00:16:56,000 --> 00:16:58,920
with too many suffocating
regulatory burdens.

386
00:16:59,000 --> 00:17:00,920
Now is not the time

387
00:17:01,000 --> 00:17:03,040
to shove restrictive
federal mandates

388
00:17:03,120 --> 00:17:06,640
down the throats of American businesses
and American families.

389
00:17:06,720 --> 00:17:09,680
This bill is unfair,
anti-business,

390
00:17:09,760 --> 00:17:12,800
anti-growth, invasive,
deathly expensive...

391
00:17:12,880 --> 00:17:14,760
"I say this to the House,

392
00:17:14,840 --> 00:17:17,400
"if we allow new mothers
