507
00:22:03,000 --> 00:22:04,520
What we're saying is,

508
00:22:04,600 --> 00:22:07,120
you deserve
the very best, moms.

509
00:22:07,200 --> 00:22:09,200
You're just not gonna get it.

510
00:22:09,280 --> 00:22:11,800
Happy Mother's Day.

511
00:22:14,000 --> 00:22:17,360
And finally tonight,
let's talk about Japan,

512
00:22:17,440 --> 00:22:20,000
a nation so vibrant,
not even Sofia Coppola

513
00:22:20,080 --> 00:22:22,040
and the band Air
could make it boring.

514
00:22:22,120 --> 00:22:24,200
Japan, like every country,

515
00:22:24,280 --> 00:22:26,320
has struggled
to engage its people

516
00:22:26,400 --> 00:22:28,320
with government programs
and services.

517
00:22:28,400 --> 00:22:31,640
That's why they've come up with a
quintessentially Japanese solution,

518
00:22:31,720 --> 00:22:32,960
mascots.

519
00:22:33,040 --> 00:22:34,920
These are mascot characters

520
00:22:35,000 --> 00:22:37,200
created for local districts
throughout Japan

521
00:22:37,280 --> 00:22:38,920
to promote the areas.

522
00:22:39,000 --> 00:22:42,800
Apparently, there are now
over 1,500 such mascots.

523
00:22:42,880 --> 00:22:45,920
1,500 mascots !

524
00:22:46,000 --> 00:22:48,360
So if you're in Japan
and you throw a rock,

525
00:22:48,440 --> 00:22:49,920
you'll probably hit one.

526
00:22:50,000 --> 00:22:51,560
And you'll know it
when it happens

527
00:22:51,640 --> 00:22:54,160
because you'll probably hear
an adorable squeaking sound.

528
00:22:54,240 --> 00:22:57,040
And it's not just
local districts' tourism boards.

529
00:22:57,120 --> 00:22:59,680
There are official mascots
for everything.

530
00:22:59,760 --> 00:23:02,280
Some cities
have dozens of mascots.

531
00:23:02,360 --> 00:23:05,320
This is Noruran,
a mascot for a train line.

532
00:23:05,400 --> 00:23:08,000
And this is Katakkuri-chan,
the mascot

533
00:23:08,080 --> 00:23:10,400
for a notorious
Japanese prison.

534
00:23:10,480 --> 00:23:11,920
That's right.

535
00:23:12,000 --> 00:23:14,640
Their prisons have mascots.

536
00:23:14,720 --> 00:23:17,080
And you've got to admit,
The Shawshank Redemption

537
00:23:17,160 --> 00:23:19,480
would be a very different movie
if every now and then

538
00:23:19,560 --> 00:23:21,880
that thing was walking around
in the background.

539
00:23:21,960 --> 00:23:23,520
That's a different film.

540
00:23:23,600 --> 00:23:26,120
That's a very different film.

541
00:23:26,200 --> 00:23:29,920
And the thing is,
mascots can be big business.

542
00:23:30,000 --> 00:23:33,440
Just look at Kumamon,
one area's lovable bear mascot.

543
00:23:33,520 --> 00:23:36,920
He has brought in
an estimated $1.2 billion

544
00:23:37,000 --> 00:23:38,800
over two years.

545
00:23:38,880 --> 00:23:41,960
And if you're wondering why,
take a look at this.

546
00:23:49,240 --> 00:23:50,400
He loves Kumamoto a lot

547
00:23:53,520 --> 00:23:54,520
That's it.

548
00:23:54,640 --> 00:23:56,880
I am done interacting
with humans now.

549
00:23:56,960 --> 00:23:58,760
If you ever want
to talk to me,

550
00:23:58,840 --> 00:24:02,440
wear a Kumamon outfit
or get the fuck out.

551
00:24:02,520 --> 00:24:05,520
And the thing, he's not even
the most popular.

552
00:24:05,600 --> 00:24:07,360
That title goes
to Funassyi,

553
00:24:07,440 --> 00:24:09,160
a giant genderless pear

554
00:24:09,240 --> 00:24:11,760
representing the city
of Funabashi.

555
00:24:11,840 --> 00:24:14,840
And not only does Funassyi
hold press conferences,

556
00:24:14,920 --> 00:24:18,200
he does some pretty incredible
TV appearances.

557
00:24:18,280 --> 00:24:20,400
Let me show you just one.

558
00:24:30,480 --> 00:24:32,480
I don't know...

559
00:24:32,560 --> 00:24:35,280
I don't know why anyone
is still watching this show

560
00:24:35,360 --> 00:24:40,080
or any other show now that they know
that that video exists somewhere.

561
00:24:40,160 --> 00:24:42,240
Mascots have become
such a feature

562
00:24:42,320 --> 00:24:45,360
of political life in Japan
that foreign embassies

563
00:24:45,440 --> 00:24:47,760
are even being compelled
to play along.

564
00:24:47,840 --> 00:24:49,920
The Israeli embassy in Japan

565
00:24:50,000 --> 00:24:52,560
